      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrating QoI change less than 5% between medium and fine mesh. Gradation 2 required at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed: coarse (2.1M cells), medium (5.8M cells), fine (14.2M cells). Relative hemolysis index changed by 3.1% between medium and fine mesh, satisfying the 5% convergence criterion. GCI computed as 1.8%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must be conducted under conditions representative of the COU operating envelope, with documented flow rates and rotational speeds matching simulation inputs. Gradation 2 required at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis measurements were sourced from the FDA benchmark dataset, which covers nominal operating conditions at 2500 and 3500 RPM. However, the CPB COU requires evaluation across 5 flow-speed combinations spanning 1800–4200 RPM; the available experimental data covers only 2 of these 5 operating points. The two uncovered operating points at 1800 RPM and 4200 RPM represent the low-shear and high-shear extremes respectively. Interpolation was used to infer hemolysis at untested conditions. This constitutes a partial coverage of the required test envelope, achieving Gradation 1 rather than the required Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison of model outputs to experimental measurements with defined metrics and uncertainty bounds. Gradation 2 required at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index compared quantitatively using normalized RMS error and Bland-Altman analysis. Mean prediction error 8.3% with 95% limits of agreement ±12.1%. Comparison conducted at all available experimental operating points with documented uncertainty propagation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
